# Rate Limiting Rules

## Setup

```ts
// app.module.ts
ThrottlerModule.forRootAsync({
  imports: [ConfigModule],
  useFactory: (config: ConfigService) => ([
    {
      name: 'default',
      ttl: 60000,   // 1 minute window
      limit: 60,    // 60 requests per window
    },
    {
      name: 'strict',
      ttl: 60000,
      limit: 5,     // 5 requests per minute (auth endpoints)
    },
  ]),
  inject: [ConfigService],
}),

// Apply globally
{ provide: APP_GUARD, useClass: ThrottlerGuard },
```

---

## Endpoint-Specific Limits

```ts
// Default: 60/min (inherited from global)
@Get('users')
findAll() { ... }

// Strict: auth endpoints
@Throttle({ strict: { ttl: 60000, limit: 5 } })
@Post('auth/login')
login() { ... }

@Throttle({ strict: { ttl: 60000, limit: 5 } })
@Post('auth/register')
register() { ... }

@Throttle({ strict: { ttl: 60000, limit: 3 } })
@Post('auth/forgot-password')
forgotPassword() { ... }

// Skip throttle for internal/webhook routes
@SkipThrottle()
@Post('webhooks/stripe')
stripeWebhook() { ... }
```

---

## Limits by Endpoint Type

| Endpoint Type              | Limit     | TTL     |
|----------------------------|-----------|---------|
| General API                | 60 req    | 1 min   |
| Auth (login/register)      | 5 req     | 1 min   |
| Forgot password / OTP      | 3 req     | 1 min   |
| File upload                | 10 req    | 1 min   |
| Search / autocomplete      | 30 req    | 1 min   |
| Admin endpoints            | 120 req   | 1 min   |
| Webhooks (skip throttle)   | unlimited | —       |

